    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWould it be reasonable for neovim to fire an event (e.g., GitConflictDetected) when a file is opened and it includes Git conflict markers e.g., \r\n```\r\n<<<<<<< HEAD:file.txt\r\nHello world\r\n=======\r\n``` \r\nIt will facilitate automating handling of conflicts e.g., loading an appropriate plugin or aborting certain actions. \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nevent fired when a git conflict marker detected.",
    "closed_at": "2023-11-16T01:35:40Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Seems way to specific for a dedicated autocommand. Just use `BufRead` and detect the conflict markers?",
